David,

The problem is that the version of Python you have was compiled with 
Visual C++.  If you want to build the Cantera Python extension module 
with cygwin/g++, you will need to get the source distribution of Python 
and build it also with cygwin. Alternatively, if you only plan to use 
Python to process .cti files, you can specify a minimal Python 
installation, in which the extension module is skipped.

Dave

